reportCellPad(25.10)                                      reportCellPad(25.10)

Name
       reportCellPad  -  Prints the number of cells, which contain user-speci-
       fied padding, to the log file

Syntax
       reportCellPad

       [-help]

       [-cell <cellName>]

       [-file <fileName>]

       Prints the number of cells, which contain  user-specified  padding,  to
       the  log file. Optionally, you can obtain a complete list of cells with
       their padding information in a file using the -file parameter. The for-
       mat of this file is same as used in the  specifyCellPad  command,  that
       is,

       <cellName> <padding >(in grid units)

Parameters
       -cell <cellName>
              Specifies the cell name to report padding.

       -file <fileName>
              Specifies the generated file name to dump cell padding.

       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes type and default in-
              formation for each reportCellPad parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command: man reportCellPad.

Examples
       The following steps show the usage of reportCellPad command:

              * Specify the following padding using  the  specifyCellPad  com-
                mand:

                specifyCellPad FF_SCAN 2

                specifyCellPad DFFSHQX1 5

                specifyCellPad DFFSRX4 4

              * Run the reportCellPad command. After running this command, you
                get  the  value  3 and the following message is printed to the
                log file:

                3 cells have padding.

              * To print the above-mentioned list of cells in the file myfile,
                specify the following command:

                reportCellPad -file myfile

              * After running this command, the following contents  of  myfile
                are displayed:

                FF_SCAN 2

                DFFSHQX1 5

                DFFSRX4 4

                # 3 cells have padding.

